Package: sticky
Type: Package
Title: Persist attributes through data operateions
Description: In base R, attributes disappear when the objects they described
    are mutated, filtered, sliced, etc.  By marking objects 'sticky', attributes
    become resilent to common data manipulation operations: subset, extend,
    append, etc. or when inserted into or extracted from recursive (i.e. list-
    or table-like) objects. 'sticky' works on both atomic and recursive objects.
Version: 0.2
Date: 2016-05-15
